cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.STAT, cs.CL 

The paper deals with uncertainty quantification in deep neural networks for classification tasks. This topic is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), statistics (cs.STAT), and natural language processing (cs.CL). However, since the paper focuses on classification tasks, we can rule out cs.CL as a less likely category. Among the remaining four categories, cs.LG and cs.AI are the most likely since they are the broadest categories that cover deep learning and uncertainty quantification. cs.CV is also a likely category since it deals with image classification, which is a common application of deep learning. Finally, cs.STAT is a possible category since it deals with statistical methods for data analysis, which is relevant to the proposed Dirichlet mixture approach.
